        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 12:04AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1204 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Okaton, or near Murdo, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Murdo, Draper, and Okaton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
central South Dakota.</instruction>
